    "headline": "Wall Street follows global markets lower as Iran war briefly pushes crude prices near $120 a barrel",
    "summary": "Wall Street futures followed global markets lower early Monday and oil prices briefly spiked to nearly $120 per barrel as the Iran war intensified, threatening production and shipping in the Middle East.  Global markets also took a beating, with Japan’s benchmark Nikkei 225 index plunging more than 5% and markets across Europe losing between 2% and 3%.  Shares of major U.S. airlines continued their descent as spiking fuel prices are projected to eat into their profits.",
